listing.title: Thai Delight
listing.crossstreet: Between Ontario Dr and Hollenbeck Ave/N Stelling Rd
listing.latestreview: There are lots and lots of restaurants in the area that offer just about any ethnic cuisine you can imagine. So how did we end up at Thai Delight? Our GPS said this was the closest place to us when we decided we needed to find somewhere for lunch. We walked in in the middle of the lunch rush and noticed that they had a steady crowd at the noon hour.While standing in line waiting for our table, I was talking to a "local" who told me that the food was great, but dont expect too much in the way of service while in the restaurant.There is no way to understate the truth of that tip. There were only two people working the dining area. One was a middle-aged male, who was probably the owner or manager of the restaurant. He would race through the dining area and quickly pick-up or pass-out plates. He also appeared to be someone who should not skip taking blood-pressure medicine as he appeared close to going over the edge.The second server was a very polite female who probably had 10 tables more than she could handle. We requested a babys highchair then ordered. When the food arrived, it became apparent that we needed to scout around the dining room and find our own highchair, which we did.The food was different from what we expected. That doesnt mean that it was bad, only different. Most of the Thai restaurants we frequently visit have lots of rich flavors in their foods. The food was good, but lacked that extra burst of flavors we enjoy at some other Thai restaurants. Again, the food was good, just not exceptional.This is where things start to slide down hill a little. We complete the meal, and wait for our server to bring the bill. We wait and wait and wait. We also notice that we are not alone in the waiting game. The two servers are overwhelmed in getting food out to the ot

listing.latestreview: This was the second time I went to this restaurant. First time with my family on July 17, 2010. We ordered goat karahi, nihari, goat biryani and naan. All were good except for biryani. It was stale and bad. I am sure that this was not fresh. Most likely a day old. They were still feeding people this food that could make people sick. We pointed this out to them and they did not even say sorry. Just did not charge us for biryani. I do not think I will go there again. I wonder where the health department is and how do they check these things out. I will tell the patrons to be careful about this restaurant.

listing.latestreview: We had dinner at this location on Saturday night and I ordered their new California Chicken Salad. From the first bite I was thinking the dressing wasnt right with the salad because it tasted wrong. About 1/2 way through (we were trying to make a show so I didnt have time to ask for something else) I came to the conclusion the Feta tasted spoiled. It tasted like blue cheese...Feta tastes nothing like blue cheese so I knew something was wrong. :( Ive had problems since about 4hrs after the meal...been in bed ever since. :( I love the Outback but not so much this time! They did comp the salad but I am not only out sick time from work, I was supposed to have a photo shoot today that would pay me $200. :( x A LOT....

listing.crossstreet: Near the intersection of N De Anza Blvd and Alves Dr
listing.desc: From its establishment, there has been a single challenge for the Mandarin Gourmet: offer the public gourmet Chinese cuisine in an elegant environment, pampered by an attentive staff. Each member of the staff at the Mandarin Gourmet perceives as the number one goal, to provide the customer with the best possible service, food, and atmosphere. listing.latestreview: I have been going to Mandarin since it was changed over from Bobs Big Boy. The food is the best, (I think ever better than her sisters in San Jose) Fantastic service. I bring my friends and customers here especially when I want to impress them. Lunch special is inexpensive and Dinner is extraordinary for the price. You simply will not find another restaurant that will cater to you like Mandarin. After all fine food without service is still just takout. If you ever wanted to see how customers are treated at the very finest places, come and experience it here.

listing.desc: Big, meaty sandwiches, stuffed with the freshest, ingredients; California avocados mashed daily; Abundant quantities of all beef pastrami,; 97 percent fat free roast beef; 98 percent fat free slow roasted turkey; 100 percent natural chicken (antibiotic free); Fresh Baked Artisan bread; Togo's homemade albacore tuna and chicken salad; Fresh made Santa Fe Chicken salad and salad wraps; Savory soups
listing.latestreview: Im usually not a sandwich kinda guy because Ive had quite a few bad experiences.. with that said, when youre with a pretty girl and she wants a sandwich, you go where she wants to go. This place was actually amazing compared to some of the other places Ive been to based on a few things:1) This store smells great inside. First thing I noticed through the door was the smell, not like a perfume either, just a fresh smell.2) I felt like my sandwich-maker person actually cared about the job. I was greeted on the way in, after I ordered they clarified and talked through the process of making the sandwich to make sure everything was right, and were friendly about it too. No attitudes, which was nice.3) The food just tasted good. I have a pretty particular stomach that gets upset very easy. Had Turkey, Avacado, Bacon, and Veggies with nothing "bad" afterwards. Woo!

listing.desc: BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse is the place to go for feel-good American food such as baby back ribs, sandwiches, hamburgers and pizzas. Top it off with their craft beers and you are ready to enjoy the good life without breaking the bank. Take a sip of the Russian Imperial Stout and then relish Boneless Wings, Spinach Stuffed Mushrooms, Mini-Bruschetta, Crispy Fried Artichokes or Gourmet Mac and Cheese. With plenty of desserts and an extensive kid's menu, this place is a favorite with the whole family.

My friend went to get a manager and the he came out and said sorry and asked if he coulg get us anything...he offered a party size pizookie and when the check came another hour later, they charged us $18 for that pizookie, AND 17% gratuity even after we told them it was the worst service ever!!!!!!! I hope they go out of business soon. Save yourself and go to the one on blossom hill.
